OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FThe Belgians getting the   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fright to disconnect from   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fwork                       
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Although she once hoped to be          
OL,6, professional chef, in the end Delphine 
OL,7, opted to be a civil servant.           
OL,9,FShe still loves to make time to cook   
OL,10,Fthough: "It's one of my passions!"     
OL,12,FThe 36-year-old is preparing dinner for
OL,13,Fher friends, Catherine and Roch. It's  
OL,14,FHachis Parmentier, a dish of mince and 
OL,15,Fmashed potato - sometimes likened to a 
OL,16,Fshepherd's pie.                        
OL,18,FAs she stirs the onions, she tells me  
OL,19,Fshe welcomes the fact that many civil  
OL,20,Fservants in Belgium are getting the    
OL,21,Fright to disconnect.                   
